==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: motor-driven
<hw>mo`tor-driv`en</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>Driven or
actuated by a motor, esp. by an individual electric motor. An electric
motor forms an integral part of many machine tools in numerous modern
machine shops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

